Speaking about prevention (for the specific case of the like button), I have privoxy (1) setup to disable fb plugins with rules like these:<p>{+block{Facebook "like" and similar tracking URLs.}}
www.facebook.com/(extern|plugins)/(login_status|like(box)?|activity|fan)\.php<p>{+block{Stupid facebook xd_proxy.php.}}
<a href="http://static.ak.fbcdn.net/connect/xd_proxy.php.*" rel="nofollow">http://static.ak.fbcdn.net/connect/xd_proxy.php.*</a><p>The second one also removes an annoyance I see from time to time when I bypass the proxy which makes the page request again and again that xd_proxy.php file.<p>If I really want to like something, I disable the proxy and reload the page. I use Proxy SwitchySharp (2) for chrome to do the setup for me in pages I visit often.<p>1: <a href="http://www.privoxy.org/" rel="nofollow">http://www.privoxy.org/</a>
2: <a href="https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/dpplabbmogkhghncfbfdeeokoefdjegm" rel="nofollow">https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/dpplabbmogkhghncfb...</a>
